01:45.730 --> 01:47.430
mesh quite yet.

01:47.800 --> 01:54.980
If I hit the tab key you can see that we're still at the original subdivision level here in edit mode

01:55.750 --> 02:03.410
but if we look at it in wireframe we can see all of the subdivided polygons there.

02:03.850 --> 02:08.740
So with three sculped subdivisions I'll see what I can do with this.

02:08.740 --> 02:16.120
Now the pre-view subdivisions is what you can see here in the viewport in Object mode.

02:16.120 --> 02:23.650
The sculped subdivisions is what you can see over here in sculped mode if I click on object mode I can

02:23.650 --> 02:31.780
change it to sculpt mode and then the render subdivisions is what you'll see when the scene is actually

02:31.840 --> 02:33.070
rendered out.

02:33.100 --> 02:39.250
Now that I've clicked on the sculped tool you can see that I've got my sculped tools panel over here

02:40.210 --> 02:40.870
up at the top.

